sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / CI
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Webhook as Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Controller as Controller Manager<br/>8080/TCP metrics
    participant Driver as Spark Driver Pod
    participant Executors as Spark Executor Pods<br/>7078/TCP, 7079/TCP

    Note over User,Executors: Flow 1: SparkApplication Submission

    User->>K8sAPI: POST SparkApplication CR<br/>HTTPS/443 | Bearer token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Mutate SparkApplication<br/>HTTPS/9443 | API server mTLS
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Defaulted SparkApplication
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Validate SparkApplication<br/>HTTPS/9443 | API server mTLS
    Webhook->>K8sAPI: Check ResourceQuota<br/>HTTPS/443 | SA token
    K8sAPI-->>Webhook: Quota info
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation result

    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event: SparkApplication created
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create driver pod (spark-submit)<br/>HTTPS/443 | SA token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Mutate Pod (label selector)<br/>HTTPS/9443 | API server mTLS
    Note over Webhook: Injects: volumes, env vars,<br/>sidecars, Prometheus config,<br/>security contexts, scheduling
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated Pod spec
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Pod created

    Driver->>K8sAPI: Create executor pods<br/>HTTPS/443 | spark-operator-spark SA token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Mutate executor Pods<br/>HTTPS/9443 | API server mTLS
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated executor specs
    Driver->>Executors: Task execution<br/>TCP/7078 (driver-rpc)<br/>TCP/7079 (blockmanager)
    Executors-->>Driver: Task results

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create UI Service ({app}-ui-svc:4040)<br/>HTTPS/443 | SA token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update SparkApplication status<br/>HTTPS/443 | SA token

    Note over User,Executors: Flow 2: ScheduledSparkApplication Cron Execution

    User->>K8sAPI: POST ScheduledSparkApplication CR<br/>HTTPS/443 | Bearer token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Mutate + Validate<br/>HTTPS/9443 | API server mTLS
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validated

    loop Cron Schedule
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create SparkApplication CR<br/>HTTPS/443 | SA token
        Note over Controller: Applies concurrency policy:<br/>Allow / Forbid / Replace
        K8sAPI->>Controller: Triggers SparkApplication reconcile
        Note over Controller,Executors: (Same as Flow 1 from here)
    end

    Note over User,Executors: Flow 3: SparkConnect Server Lifecycle

    User->>K8sAPI: POST SparkConnect CR<br/>HTTPS/443 | Bearer token
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event: SparkConnect created

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ConfigMap (executor pod template)<br/>HTTPS/443 | SA token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create server Pod<br/>HTTPS/443 | SA token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Service (4 ports)<br/>HTTPS/443 | SA token

    participant Client as SparkConnect Client

    Client->>Driver: Spark Connect protocol<br/>TCP/15002 | No auth
    Driver->>Executors: Task execution<br/>TCP/7078, 7079
    Executors-->>Driver: Results
    Driver-->>Client: Response
